nly reduce carbon assimilation but also the probability of catching larger prey. The amount of insect-derived nitrogen decreases to 46\%, and Dionaea becomes increasingly dependent on N-supply from the soil. Competition for both light and N may cause the near disappearance of Dionaea in older stages of the fire succession.},
